       =20
  [1] Depends how you count. The pro forma financials on page 70 of its rec=
ent S-1 show a loss from operations for Trump Media of $16 million and a ne=
t loss of $58.2 million. But the pro forma combination of Trump Media and t=
he special purpose acquisition company that bought it had a net loss of $10=
0.7 million, counting things like the legal bills of the SPAC.=20


  [2] Page 199: =E2=80=9CDigital World=E2=80=99s management concluded that =
an initial valuation of $875 million, with the potential for an additional =
earnout of $825 million, was a reasonable assessment for TMTG=E2=80=99s ent=
erprise valuation in the Business Combination transaction.=E2=80=9D


  [3] Page 202. Also they average =E2=80=9Cmonthly active user growth of 58=
.3%=E2=80=9D in the first year. But the prospectus noted: =E2=80=9CThis inf=
ormation has inherent limitations because it required an estimation of MAUs=
 and MAU% to align with other comparable companies. However, TMTG has neith=
er currently nor previously tracked such metrics as a Key Performance Indic=
ator (=E2=80=98KPI=E2=80=99). As a result, these estimations lack any histo=
rical trends and were based solely on DWAC=E2=80=99s management estimations=
, which utilized public data of the comparable companies mentioned above.=
=E2=80=9D That is: The board valued Trump Media in part by comparing its MA=
Us to those of other social media companies, but Trump Media doesn=E2=80=99=
t *track* MAUs?


  [4] The US Securities and Exchange Commission says: =E2=80=9CThe appearan=
ce of a security on a threshold list does not necessarily mean that there h=
as been abusive =E2=80=98naked=E2=80=99 short selling or any impermissible =
trading in the stock. Delivery failures can be caused by both long and shor=
t sales.=E2=80=9D


  [5] Maybe not =E2=80=9CJane Street vs. Millennium=E2=80=9D per se, but wh=
o knows. =E2=80=9CBig market-making firm finds easy picking in Indian optio=
ns markets=E2=80=9D does sound a *little* like =E2=80=9Cyoung men love gamb=
ling.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CRetail investors make up about 35% of option trades=
 in India,=E2=80=9D=20
notes Bloomberg, in a story about that Jane Street trade, =E2=80=9Cwith the=
 market regulator estimating that 90% of active retail traders lose money o=
n derivatives.=E2=80=9D


  [6] And except Avi Eisenberg, but look where that got him.


  [7] The numbers here are drawn loosely from this Patrick McKenzie post on=
