<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The general form of=C2=A0consumer financial ar=
bitrage is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you buy stuff at a store with a cr=
edit card, the store will pay your credit card company a fee of, say, 1.4% =
of the price.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background=
-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you have a rewards credit card=
, your credit card company will pass some of that fee back to you, often 1%=
 of the price. If you have a nice card and do things just right, you could =
get 2% or even more.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If the stuff =
you buy has a stable market price with a bid/ask spread tighter than 1% (or=
 whatever rebate you=E2=80=99re getting), you can resell it and keep the 1%=
.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem is that there are not many consume=
r goods like that. There is not a deep liquid resale market, with tight bid=
/ask spreads, for, like, the milk you just got at the supermarket.=C2=A0If =
you could go to a store and buy <em>hundred-dollar bills=C2=A0</em>with a c=
redit card, then you=E2=80=99d go buy 100 hundred-dollar bills on your cred=
it card for $10,000, use the=C2=A0bills to pay your $10,000 credit card bil=
l, collect $100 of cash-back rewards, and do that again and again. But you =
can=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0Most of the time=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/35121691.265351/aHR0cHM6Ly93YWxsZXRodWIuY29tL2VkdS9=
jYy9jYW4teW91LWJ1eS1hLW1vbmV5LW9yZGVyLXdpdGgtYS1jcmVkaXQtY2FyZC8yMDQwNw/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa503d54b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">buying cash substitutes with a cred=
it card</a> will run into restrictions or fees that make the arbitrage not =
work.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What about buying gold bars? Intuitively=C2=A0=
it seems like the answer would be =E2=80=9Cthe price of gold is volatile, a=
nd the bid/ask in retail gold transactions is=C2=A0higher than 1%, so don=
=E2=80=99t do this, come on.=E2=80=9D Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/35121691.265351/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5=
hbmNlL2ludmVzdGluZy9zZWxsaW5nLWNvc3Rjby1nb2xkLWJhcnMtZjE0ZTk2NmY_bW9kPWhwX2=
